\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. C. dentatus} (Forskål) Vahl,{\i  Symb. Bot.}{\b  1}: 69 (1790). Glandular annual, with more or less lanate or villous, arachnoid indumentum. Cauline leaves lanceolate to ovate-lanceolate, pinnatifid to pinnatisect, with spiny margin. Capitula oblong-ovoid. Inner involucral bracts with scarious, ovate-lanceolate, dentate apical appendages. Corolla pale violet to pinkish-purple. Achenes broadly obpyramidal. Pappus of long, brown, linear, ciliate scales, at least twice as long as the achene. 2n = 20.{\i  S. part of  Balkan peninsula, Aegean region.} Bu Cr Gr Ju Tu.
