\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b dentatus}: Plant densely glandular, with lanate and arachnoid indumentum. Leaves greyish. Outer involucral bracts not more than 1½ times as long as the inner, erect or somewhat patent, with short spines. Inner pappus-scales usually shorter than the outer.{\i  Throughout the range of the species, except the south.}
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b ruber} (Link) Hanelt, {\i Feddes Repert.}{\b  67}: 98 (1963) ({\i Kentrophyllum rubrum} Link): Plant more or less glandular, with sparsely villous and arachnoid indumentum. Leaves greyish or green. Outer involucral bracts at least twice as long as the inner, strongly patent or deflexed, with long spines. Most or all inner pappus-scales as long as the outer.{\i  S. Greece and Aegean region}.
\par 

